<h1>Call for Judges</h1>  
</div>
<div>
<p>
	Check back soon&nbsp;to submit a 2013 judge application, which we will accept online between July 23, 2012, and August 17, 2012.</p>
The Innovations Design and Engineering Awards program recognizes the most innovative consumer electronics products the 32 categories and has become a hallmark for the best-designed products in consumer technology. Download the&nbsp;<a href="http://staging.cesweb.org/cesweb/media/CESWeb/Innovation%20Awards/General%20Innovations%20Files/2012-Category-Guide.pdf">awards category guide</a>&nbsp;that includes examples of eligible products within a category to assist you in selecting the categories you feel most qualified to judge.<br />
<br />
<br />

</div>

<div class="sub-content-header">Innovations Design and Engineering Judging Process</div>

<p>Each awards category is judged by a three-member panel consisting of an independent industrial designer, independent engineer or industry analyst and a member of the trade press. The judging process is conducted online and will begin September 24, 2012, and end on October 5, 2012. We have determined that it takes approximately 10-15 minutes to evaluate an entry. Depending on how many entries are in a category, judging may take anywhere from 3-15 hours to complete.<br />
<br />
</p>
<div class="sub-content-header">Innovations Judge Benefits</div>

<p><ul>
	<li>
		Be the first to see the newest products in the CE industry</li>
	<li>
		Volunteer and network with other preeminent industry professionals</li>
	<li>
		Invitation to the CES Unveiled@ NY at the Pre-CES New York Press Preview where the Innovations honorees are announced</li>
	<li>
		Invitation to the CES Unveiled, The Official Press Event of the International CES</li>
	<li>
		Recognition throughout the year on CESweb.org/Innovations</li>
	<li>
		Special ribbon to wear on-site at CES to designate your status as an Innovations Judge</li>
	<li>
		Questions? Contact us at&nbsp;<a href="mailto:Innovations@ce.org">Innovations@ce.org</a></li>
</ul>
</p>

